        | &nbsp;How do I read a memo?
      p(id="how-do-i-read-a-memo-answer")
        p To read a memo for a specific Nano Block, all you need to know is the Nano Block's hash. This is a unique identifier for each Nano Block on the Nano Network. Once you have the hash, simply enter it into the search box at the top of this website and hit enter.
        p If a memo has been written for that block, you will see the message. If the memo has been encrypted, you will see ciphertext and have the option to enter your private key to decrypt the message if you were the intended recipient.
        p If no memo has been written, you will only see the details of the Nano Block. If the Nano Block is yours, there will be a link to write and save a memo for that Nano Block.
