      h5(id="is-nanomemo-decentralized")
        a(href="#is-nanomemo-decentralized" class="link-muted")
          i(class="bi bi-link-45deg")
        | &nbsp;Is NanoMemo Decentralized?
      p(id="is-nanomemo-decentralized-answer")
        p No, NanoMemo is not decentralized. However, at this point we believe it does not need to be decentralized. In cyber security we speak of Confidentiality, Integrity, and Availability. NanoMemo offers condientiality through encrypted memos. NanoMemo offers integrity through digital signatures on memos. We, however, do not offer availability if the NanoMemo server goes away. Decentralized sharing of memos would require a lot of network and resource overhead. However, availability of a memo (not the NanoMemo server) exists as you can simply make copies of the memos saved at NanoMemo.cc. Because of the digital signatures and potential encryption, anyone can store a NanoMemo and its authenticity still be proven.
